This analysis detects memory access after free.
1. Where is memory released?
2. Where is the subsequent read/write/use through the same pointer or alias?
3. Is the pointer reassigned to valid memory before use?
4. Are free and use operations reachable on the same execution path?
Use the tools to verify alias flow and path reachability.
If use cannot occur after free on any reachable path, there is no issue.
Only flag if freed memory can be accessed afterward.
